verbose_text: Cholesterol 25-hydroxylase (CH25H) and oxysterol 7alpha-hydroxy-lase (CYP7B1), which are enzymes required for the biosynthesis of GPR183 ligand 7alpha,25-OHC, are highly expressed in spleen and LN stromal cells.
